The paper deals with computational problems related to preference profiles, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The measurement of distance between preference profiles and nicely structured profiles involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), and the classification of problem variants with respect to their computational complexity is a fundamental topic in theoretical computer science (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's focus on computational tractability and NP-hardness suggests a connection to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
